## Plumbing challenges in Kashmir homes

Kashmir's climate — freezing winters, seasonal rainfall, and older building stock in parts of Srinagar — puts extra demand on home plumbing. Hard water can affect taps and geysers; overhead tanks and booster pumps are common; hidden leaks behind walls may only show up as damp patches or low pressure. Attempting DIY fixes on pressurized lines often makes the problem worse.

When you book through Panun Kaergar, you are hiring a professional who understands residential plumbing in local conditions. Partners on our platform arrive with proper tools and can advise whether a repair is sufficient or parts need replacement. You can describe the issue when booking — a dripping tap, a slow drain, no hot water from the geyser, water pooling under a sink — and the assigned plumber comes prepared for the visit.

For families with elderly members or homes preparing for guests during Eid and wedding season, reliable plumbing is essential. Panun Kaergar's review system helps the community identify plumbers who consistently deliver quality work across Srinagar.

