## Tips before your plumber visit in Srinagar

A little preparation helps your booking go smoothly and saves time on site:

- **Turn off the main water supply** if you have an active leak and know where the valve is.
- **Clear access** under sinks, behind commodes, and around the geyser or overhead tank.
- **Note when the problem started** and whether it is getting worse — useful for diagnosis.
- **List all issues** in one booking if they are in the same visit — for example, a leaking tap and a slow bathroom drain.
- **Be home or have someone available** to show the plumber the problem areas and approve the work.

If the job requires materials — a new tap, pipes, or fittings — your partner can advise on what is needed. Some plumbers carry common parts; for specialised items, they may recommend local purchase or a follow-up visit once parts are ready.

